# GoLive Project Walkthrough

## Project Overview
GoLive is a modern live-streaming platform built with Next.js 14, Supabase, and Tailwind CSS. It features real-time chat, video uploading, user profiles, and a robust community engagement system.

## Key Features Implemented
### 1. Core Platform
- **Authentication**: Email/Password login with Supabase Auth.
- **Video Player**: Custom video player with theater mode.
- **Live Streaming**: Simulated RTMP streaming interface.
- **Upload System**: Drag-and-drop video upload with thumbnail support.

### 2. Community & Growth
- **"Momentum Engine"**: Automated growth hacking system that simulates engagement (views/likes) for new uploads.
- **Comments & Chat**: Real-time interaction using Supabase Realtime.
- **Subscriptions**: Follow/Unfollow functionality.

### 3. Polish & Performance
- **Server Components**: Refactored major pages (Home, Watch) for SEO and performance.
- **Responsive Design**: Mobile-first UI with a premium dark mode aesthetic.
- **Type Safety**: strict TypeScript interfaces for all data models.

